2. THE UNCHOSEN PATHS OF GATE 2 (what burned while they were in Riften)
=====================================================================
DARKWATER CROSSING -- CONSUMED.
  Nobody went. The roots finished the town: houses crushed, the mine
  swallowed, survivors scattered as refugees (the party met some on the
  Winterhold road). The Corrupted Taproot anchors a dead zone in central
  Eastmarch; the corruption creeps outward along the river. Spriggans and
  mutated beasts attack travelers throughout the hold's forests.

DAWNSTAR -- DRAGON CULT FORTRESS.
  Vokun holds the city intact: organized draugr enforce curfew, the raised
  Jarl sits as a thrall, Vaermina's nightmares keep the population docile.
  The Stormcloak attempt to retake it was dismantled by plague and wall --
  half the First Cohort died in the snow. Vokun watched, spent next to
  nothing, and let Alfonso's plague do his work. Dawnstar is now the
  Cult's northern anchor and a staging ground for Tier 2.

THE PLAGUE COMES HOME -- WINDHELM SEALED.
  The Cohort's survivors retreated to Windhelm carrying the disease. It
  weaponises its own cure: restoration magic feeds it. The healers made it
  an epidemic before anyone understood. The city gates are barred; the
  dying fill refugee camps outside the walls; Galmar Stone-Fist holds the
  inner barricades and sent a dying runner to Riften begging Davinia for
  aid. Ulfric is behind closed doors. This is Gate 3 Fire A.

